{
  "stem": "18581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was also question in the '30s that the British have imposed restrictions on Jewish immigration into Palestine.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you could only go as a either capitalist, for which you needed at least 1,000 sterling, which was at that time a very substantial sum, or else as a student at-- at a school of higher learning.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was too young for that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So this was our, I would say, double jeopardy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we could not actually move.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember vaguely, but there were many friends came, of course, to the railroad station to say goodbye to her.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then she joined, in [NON-ENGLISH], some other people who went.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then they took a train to Germany, to, I believe, to Italy, where they boarded a-- a ship and landed in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was a member of a kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A kibbutz of Hashomer Hatzair.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was there for a few years until few years she got married.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was a very happy Jewish home, centered around Israel and the Jewish politics and the Jewish press.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The language at home was either Hebrew or Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And sometimes, also German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when the parents didn't want us to understand, they spoke to each other in Russian.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not in German, because German was similar to Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we would-- we would have understood.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a happy home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I studied before that in a Hebrew primary and high school for part of the time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then my father decided to-- since I could not go through the full course of eight years in our town in Hebrew, because we only had the [INAUDIBLE] gymnasium, he decided that I should transfer to the-- to the Mazeikiai state gymnasium, which was in Lithuanian and had a slightly different-- slightly different program.",
      "word_count": 54
    }
  ],
